---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Skills: Turn Repeated Workflows into Reusable Moves"
  description="Learn how to use SKILL.md to turn repeated workflows into reusable playbooks that Claude Code can invoke via slash commands."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container cc-skills">
      <a class="back-link" href="/">&larr; Back to Home</a>

      <header class="detail-header">
        <h1 class="detail-title">Connect Claude Code to Tools, Teach It New Tricks, and Automate Repetitive Work</h1>
        <p class="detail-subtitle">
          We've already set up the basics for Claude Code — CLAUDE.md, memory management, context handling.
          The next stage isn't about stuffing more rules into the handbook. It's about giving Claude Code
          new abilities. Some let it see external tools, some let it follow fixed workflows, some let it
          farm out large tasks, and some automate repetitive actions. These abilities each have their own role.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Section 1: What are Skills -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Skills: Turn Repeated Workflows into Reusable "Moves"</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        A Skill is like preparing a reusable playbook for Claude Code. When you have a workflow you keep
        repeating — like "pre-deploy checklist," "write release notes in a fixed format," or "explain code
        in a beginner-friendly way" — those are perfect candidates for a Skill.
      </p>

      <div class="info-card">
        <p class="info-title">How SKILL.md differs from CLAUDE.md</p>
        <p class="info-body">
          CLAUDE.md is loaded every time; SKILL.md is loaded only when needed.<br />
          So if something isn't needed every session but only "sometimes," putting it in a Skill saves context and keeps things cleaner.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: Personal vs Project -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">First Decide: Personal Skill or Project Skill?</h2>

      <div class="compare-grid">
        <div class="compare-card">
          <p class="compare-label">Personal Skill</p>
          <p class="compare-path">~/.claude/skills/&lt;skill-folder&gt;/SKILL.md</p>
          <p class="compare-desc">Available across all your projects (personal skills).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-card compare-card--accent">
          <p class="compare-label">Project Skill</p>
          <p class="compare-path">.claude/skills/&lt;skill-folder&gt;/SKILL.md</p>
          <p class="compare-desc">Only works in the current project.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">The following example uses a project Skill.</p>

      <!-- Section 3: Tutorial (collapsible) -->
      <details class="collapsible">
        <summary class="collapsible-trigger">
          <span class="collapsible-icon"></span>
          <span class="collapsible-title">Step-by-Step: Create a Skill</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="collapsible-body">
          <p class="detail-paragraph">
            Goal: When someone pastes a piece of code, Claude Code will explain it in a beginner-friendly way —
            first the purpose, then the flow, then key variables, and finally common misconceptions.
          </p>

          <ol class="step-list">
            <li class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">1</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <h3 class="step-title">Open your project</h3>
                <p class="step-desc">Open your project folder in VS Code.</p>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">2</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <h3 class="step-title">Create the Skill folder</h3>
                <p class="step-desc">In VS Code's file explorer, create this folder path:</p>
                <pre class="code-block"><code>.claude/skills/explain-code/</code></pre>
                <div class="tip-card">
                  <p class="tip-title">That means</p>
                  <ul class="tip-list">
                    <li>Create a <code>.claude</code> folder in the project root</li>
                    <li>Create a <code>skills</code> folder inside <code>.claude</code></li>
                    <li>Create an <code>explain-code</code> folder inside <code>skills</code></li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <p class="step-desc">
                  The standard structure is "one Skill per folder, with at least one <code>SKILL.md</code> inside."
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">3</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <h3 class="step-title">Create SKILL.md</h3>
                <p class="step-desc">
                  Create <code>.claude/skills/explain-code/SKILL.md</code> and paste the following content:
                </p>
                <pre class="code-block"><code set:html={`---
name: explain-code
description: Explain code in a beginner-friendly way. Use this when teaching,
  walking through code, introducing function flows, or when a user asks
  "what does this code do."
---

When explaining code, follow this order:

1. Start with a one-sentence summary of what the code does.
2. List the execution flow step by step.
3. Highlight the most important functions, variables, or conditions.
4. If there's anything easy to confuse, proactively point it out.
5. End with a "beginner summary."

Rules:
- Use plain, conversational language
- Don't start with too much jargon
- If jargon is needed, explain it briefly
- First say "what it does," then "how it does it"
- If the code is incomplete, say so
- If appropriate, add a simple example to aid understanding

If the user pasted code, answer based on the code.
If no code was provided, ask them to share a file, function, or snippet.`} /></pre>
                <div class="note-card">
                  <p class="note-body">
                    SKILL.md has two parts: the <strong>YAML frontmatter</strong> tells Claude Code
                    what this Skill is called and when to use it; the <strong>Markdown content</strong>
                    is the actual playbook. The <code>name</code> becomes your <code>/slash-command</code>
                    (in this example, <code>/explain-code</code>), and <code>description</code> helps
                    Claude Code decide when to auto-load it.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">4</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <h3 class="step-title">Save SKILL.md</h3>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">5</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <h3 class="step-title">Start a new Claude Code conversation</h3>
                <p class="step-desc">
                  I recommend starting a fresh conversation to test. This makes it easier to confirm
                  the latest Skill content is loaded. Skills can be invoked manually or auto-loaded
                  when relevant.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">6</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <h3 class="step-title">Test the slash command</h3>
                <p class="step-desc">In the Claude Code chat, type:</p>
                <pre class="code-block code-block--command"><code>/explain-code</code></pre>
                <p class="step-desc">Then paste a short code snippet, for example:</p>
                <pre class="code-block"><code set:html={`function sumPrices(items) {
  let total = 0;
  for (const item of items) {
    total += item.price;
  }
  return total;
}`} /></pre>
                <p class="step-desc">
                  If everything is set up correctly, Claude Code will explain the code following your Skill's format.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="step-item">
              <span class="step-num">7</span>
              <div class="step-body">
                <h3 class="step-title">Test auto-loading</h3>
                <p class="step-desc">You can also skip the slash command and just type:</p>
                <pre class="code-block code-block--command"><code>Please explain this code in a beginner-friendly way</code></pre>
                <p class="step-desc">Then paste the code.</p>
                <p class="step-desc">
                  If your <code>description</code> is clear enough, Claude Code may automatically
                  recognize the request matches <code>explain-code</code> and load it on its own.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Section 4: Common Issues (collapsible) -->
      <details class="collapsible">
        <summary class="collapsible-trigger">
          <span class="collapsible-icon"></span>
          <span class="collapsible-title">Common Issues &amp; Solutions</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="collapsible-body">
          <div class="faq-list">
            <article class="faq-card">
              <h3 class="faq-q">I created the folder, but the slash command (e.g. /explain-code) doesn't work</h3>
              <p class="faq-a">
                The two most common causes: the file isn't named <code>SKILL.md</code>, or the frontmatter
                format is wrong. Every Skill needs a <code>SKILL.md</code> with both frontmatter and
                Markdown content.
              </p>
              <div class="faq-solution">
                <p class="faq-solution-label">Check these three things</p>
                <ul class="faq-solution-list">
                  <li>Is the path <code>.claude/skills/explain-code/SKILL.md</code>?</li>
                  <li>Is the filename exactly <code>SKILL.md</code>?</li>
                  <li>Does the top have <code>---</code> wrapping the frontmatter?</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="faq-card">
              <h3 class="faq-q">The folder is called explain-code — does the slash command have to be the same name?</h3>
              <p class="faq-a">
                Not necessarily. The <code>name</code> field in frontmatter becomes the slash command.
                So what really matters is the <code>name</code> in the frontmatter.
              </p>
              <div class="faq-solution">
                <p class="faq-solution-label">This is what matters</p>
                <pre class="code-block"><code set:html={`---
name: explain-code
description: ...
---`} /></pre>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="faq-card">
              <h3 class="faq-q">Can a Skill include reference files?</h3>
              <p class="faq-a">
                Yes. Skills can have supporting files alongside <code>SKILL.md</code> for Claude Code to use when needed.
              </p>
              <div class="faq-solution">
                <p class="faq-solution-label">For example</p>
                <pre class="code-block"><code set:html={`.claude/skills/explain-code/
├── SKILL.md
└── examples.md`} /></pre>
                <p class="note-body" style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">
                  You can put fixed examples or templates in there for future use.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- Summary -->
      <div class="summary-card">
        <p class="summary-title">Key Takeaways</p>
        <ul class="summary-list">
          <li><strong>SKILL.md</strong> — a playbook loaded only when needed, saving context compared to CLAUDE.md.</li>
          <li><strong>Frontmatter</strong> — <code>name</code> sets the slash command, <code>description</code> enables auto-loading.</li>
          <li><strong>Personal vs Project</strong> — personal Skills go in <code>~/.claude/skills/</code>, project Skills in <code>.claude/skills/</code>.</li>
          <li><strong>Standard structure</strong> — one Skill per folder, with at least one <code>SKILL.md</code> inside.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cc-skills {
    max-width: 52rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Header */
  .detail-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-title {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .detail-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Section headings */
  .detail-heading {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-paragraph {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .detail-paragraph strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── Collapsible sections ── */
  .collapsible {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-left: 4px solid #8b5cf6;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color var(--transition);
  }

  .collapsible[open] {
    border-top-color: #8b5cf6;
    border-right-color: #8b5cf6;
    border-bottom-color: #8b5cf6;
  }

  .collapsible-trigger {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    width: 100%;
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    user-select: none;
    transition: background-color var(--transition);
  }

  .collapsible-trigger::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .collapsible-trigger:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
  }

  .collapsible-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.25rem;
    height: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .collapsible-icon::before,
  .collapsible-icon::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    background-color: #8b5cf6;
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  .collapsible-icon::before {
    top: 50%;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 2px;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
  }

  .collapsible-icon::after {
    top: 0;
    left: 50%;
    width: 2px;
    height: 100%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .collapsible[open] .collapsible-icon::after {
    opacity: 0;
  }

  .collapsible-title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
  }

  .collapsible-body {
    padding: var(--space-6);
  }

  /* ── Info card ── */
  .info-card {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .info-title {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .info-body {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Compare grid ── */
  .compare-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }

  .compare-card {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .compare-card--accent {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
  }

  .compare-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .compare-card--accent .compare-label {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .compare-path {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    word-break: break-all;
  }

  .compare-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* ── Step list (tutorial steps) ── */
  .step-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .step-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }

  .step-body {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .step-title {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .step-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .step-desc:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ── Code blocks ── */
  .code-block {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .code-block code {
    font-family: inherit;
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    color: inherit;
  }

  .code-block--command {
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
  }

  /* ── Tip card ── */
  .tip-card {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
  }

  .tip-title {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .tip-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .tip-list li {
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    position: relative;
  }

  .tip-list li::before {
    content: '\2713';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* ── Note card (inline hint) ── */
  .note-card {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .note-body {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .note-body strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── FAQ cards ── */
  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .faq-card {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .faq-q {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-a {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .faq-solution {
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .faq-solution-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .faq-solution-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
  }

  .faq-solution-list li {
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    position: relative;
  }

  .faq-solution-list li::before {
    content: '\203A';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* ── Summary card ── */
  .summary-card {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
  }

  .summary-title {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .summary-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .summary-list li {
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    position: relative;
  }

  .summary-list li::before {
    content: '\2713';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .summary-list strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── Inline code ── */
  .detail-paragraph code,
  .tip-list code,
  .step-desc code,
  .note-body code,
  .faq-a code,
  .faq-solution-list code,
  .faq-q code,
  .info-body code,
  .summary-list code {
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
